children.text: The ceiling plasterboard has not been properly fixed/screwed.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .

The plasterboard manufacturer requires that where 1200mm wide ceiling sheets are fixed with screws and adhesive, the centre of the sheet must be screwed. It is not possible to confirm that these sheets have been fixed with adhesive, so we have to assume it has been done properly. The manufacturer also states that
‘Stud adhesive does not constitute a fixing system on its own and must be used in conjunction with screws or nails’ .
These missing fixings must be installed in accordance with the manufacturer’s requirements.
